article.headline: San Diego 92, Portland 58
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Brandon Gay had 21 points and nine rebounds as San Diego beat Portland 92-58 Thursday night. Gay, one of five Toreros who scored in double figures, went 9-for-13 from the field and made two of four from behind the 3-point line. Floyd North scored 15 for San Diego and made three of four attempt from behind the arc, Nick Lewis had 12 points and eight rebounds and Brice Vounang and Corey Belser scored 10 apiece. San Diego (10-7, 2-2 West Coast Conference) shot 59.4 percent (19-for-32) from the field in the first half on the way to a 47-19 halftime lead. Portland (13-7, 2-3) made up no ground in the second half. Ben Sullivan led the Pilots with 14 points. Pooh Jeter and Karl Aaker scored 13 apiece. San Diego shot 57.6 percent from the field to Portland's 37.7 percent, and the Toreros outrebounded the Pilots 41-27.
